<TITLE> Sahara promises killers' arrest </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 20 (bdnews24.com )  The killers of a police officer who was shot dead in old Dhaka on Tuesday morning will be "caught soon", the home minister says. Sahara Khatun was speaking after visiting Dhaka Medical College Hospital to see the body of 42-year old Goutam Roy, a sub-inspector of Banglsal Police Station. Goutam, a father of two children who came from Shyamganj in Gouripur upazila of Mymensingh, was killed when he was returning to his Wari home from work at around 2:30am, Bangsal police chief Abdul Mannan told bdnews24.com. Goutam was returning home in civilian dress in the jeep of an acquaintance, 'Azam'. Mannan said. The police chief said that Azam told the police that as the jeep came to Dholaikhal road, Goutam saw three young men and had asked him to stop the car. Goutam got out of the vehicle and searched their bodies. At one point, one of the young men shot at Goutam. Hearing gunfire, a patrol police team came to the spot and found Goutam wounded. He was rushed to DMCH where the duty doctor declared him dead. The Jeep driver Shamim Hossain was also injured in the incident and is recovering at the hospital. The home minister was accompanied to DMCH by the state minister for home Shamsul Haq Tuku, RAB director general Hasan Mahmud Khandaker and Dhaka Metropolitan Police commissioner AKM Shahidul Haque. b
